<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-152-036  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 152 036.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  Feb 1990 v7 n2 p20(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In search of the perfect branch banker. (includes a relatedarticle on branch banking in Europe after 1992)</TITLE><AUTHOR>DeBow, Yvette.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>As a result of softened regulations allowing banks to price theirservices competitively, there is a heightened emphasis on salesinstead of service, which is forcing banks to automate theirbranch banking in order to concentrate on money-generating sales.andO;Platform automation will be the most important trend in branchbanking.andP;  It will free up tellers, allowing them to concentrate onmore sophisticated sales and service functions.andP;  Interactive videobanking kiosks will relieve tellers of chores such as checkcashing, bill payment, cash dispensing, check reorders and stoppayments.andP;  Banks are also realizing that automation alone will nottransform tellers into sales people, and they must provideextensive training programs to make the systems work.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BankingBank Teller TerminalsAutomationBranch BankingSalesmen and SalesmanshipMarketing.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Branch automation vendors. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>